did.unittitle: Jacques Vallee UFO and paranormal phenomena papers
did.abstract: The collection includes background files, correspondence, field notes, and press documents collected by Vallee between 1960 and 2015.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Jacques Vall√©e is a computer scientist, author, ufologist and astronomer conducting research in UFO topics.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Background files include relevant topics, general cases, social trends, cults, related phenomena, scientific topics relevant to ufology, assembled by Vallee in support of his research over the years. Also contains field notes and press documents about related topics such as cattle mutilations, and face-to-face meetings of NIDS and BAASS, as well as various research proposals.
Correspondence includes letters exchanged with Aime Michel, Dr. Hynek, Dr. Guerin, and many leading researchers and investigators, starting in the late 1950s to the mid 2010s.
Analysis files are planned for donation in the future, and will include research studies, often field investigations or document research about specific UFO topics.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This material is restricted by request of the donor for ten years from the date of the gift. The opening date will be Jan. 1, 2031. Several specific academic exceptions have been made and are articulated in the deed of gift. Contact woodson@rice.edu for details.
